USAGE="Usage: ${bold}pkg add PKGNAME${endcolour}

Will download and install the best match 
of PKGNAME, as well as its dependencies, 
not including builtin packages.

PKGNAME should be a valid repo package.

With ${bold}--ask${endcolour} you will get an interative list 
of all matching packages, including builtins.

With ${bold}--force${endcolour} you can re-get packages 
that are already installed.

With ${bold}-F${endcolour} it will get and download builtins too!."
